This paper deals with reinforcement learning in a complex environment with multiple agents, which is a problem commonly studied in the sub-fields of machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE), robotics (cs.RO), and control systems (cs.SY). The use of kernel-based methods and regularization networks also suggests a focus on machine learning and artificial intelligence. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG and cs.AI, followed by cs.RO, cs.SY, and cs.NE.
